==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Slime
<hw>Slime</hw> <pr>(sl⟦imac⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>slim</ets>, AS. <ets>sl⟦imac⟧m</ets>; akin to D. <ets>slijm</ets>,
G. <ets>schleim</ets>, MHG. <ets>sl⟦imac⟧men</ets> to make smooth, Icel.
<ets>sl⟦imac⟧m</ets> slime, Dan. <ets>sliim</ets>; cf. L.
<ets>limare</ets> to file, polish, <ets>levis</ets> smooth, Gr.
<?/<?/<?/; or cf. L. <ets>limus</ets> mud.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Soft,
moist earth or clay, having an adhesive quality; viscous mud.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As it [Nilus] ebbs, the seedsman⟦br⟧
Upon the <qex>slime</qex> and ooze scatters his grain.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any mucilaginous substance; any substance of a dirty
nature, that is moist, soft, and adhesive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Script.)</fld> <def>Bitumen.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Slime</qex> had they for mortar.</q> <rj><qau>Gen. xi.
3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1355 --></p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <fld>(Mining)</fld> <def>Mud containing
metallic ore, obtained in the preparatory dressing.</def>
<rj><au>Pryce.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A mucuslike substance which
exudes from the bodies of certain animals.</def>
<rj><au>Goldsmith.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Slime eel</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>See 1st
<er>Hag</er>, 4.</cd> -- <col><b>Slime pit</b></col>, <cd>a pit for the
collection of slime or bitumen.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slime</ent>⟦br⟧

